80th Street, (formerly Weisse Avenue, also known as Dry Harbor Road), west side, north of Sixtieth Avenue, showing in the foreground at the S.W. corner of the first mentioned Street and 68th Road. the J. Kissel house from 1871-1891. Henry Kissel was the owner in 1923. In the background is P.S. No. 87 a 4 story school.

April 1923
View 2: March 1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
